  "url": "sec_gt-intro.html#sec_gt-intro-43",
  "type": "Example",
  "number": "2.1.6",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  How many vertices and edges must a graph have if its degree sequence is ?    The number of vertices is easy to find: it is the number of degrees in the sequence: 7. To find the number of edges, we compute the degree sum: , so the number of edges is half this: 10.   "
