  "url": "sec_coloring.html#exercises_gt-coloring-3",
  "type": "Exercise",
  "number": "2.5.2",
  "title": "",
  "body": " Draw a graph with chromatic number 6 (i.e., which requires 6 colors to properly color the vertices). Could your graph be planar? Explain.   For example, . If the chromatic number is 6, then the graph is not planar; the 4-color theorem states that all planar graphs can be colored with 4 or fewer colors.  "
