  "body": "  Consider a set of students and a set of classes. Say and . Everyone except Dirk is in Calculus, Bob and Eva are in Discrete, and Al, Cat, and Dirk are in Statistics.  We can define a relation of is taking  and that holds of a student and class precisely if that student is taking that class. Write this relation as a subset of and draw its bipartite graph.    To write the relation precisely, we just give the set of ordered pairs: We can draw this relation as a bipartite graph:   A bipartite graph representing the \"is taking\" relation.     "
