  "title": "",
  "body": " Let be a connected graph with vertices and edges. Use mathematical induction to prove that if contains exactly one cycle (among other edges and vertices), then .  Note: this is asking you to prove a special case of Euler's formula for planar graphs, so do not use that formula in your proof.   You might want to give the proof in two parts. First prove by induction that the cycle has . Then consider what happens if the graph is more than just the cycle.  "
