  "type": "Exercise",
  "number": "3.1.7",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  In a recent survey, 80 students reported whether they liked their potatoes Mashed, French-fried, or Twice-baked. 42 liked them mashed, 46 liked French fried, and 43 liked twice baked potatoes. Additionally, 35 students liked both mashed and fried potatoes, 22 liked French fries and twice baked potatoes, 20 liked mashed and baked, and 16 liked all three styles. How many students hate potatoes? Explain why your answer is correct.        Using the principle of inclusion\/exclusion, the number of students who like their potatoes in at least one of the ways described is     Therefore there are students who do not like potatoes. You can also do this problem with a Venn diagram.      "
