  "title": "",
  "body": "multiset counting   A multiset is a collection of objects, just like a set, but can contain an object more than once (the order of the elements still doesn t matter). For example, is a multiset of size 6.   How many sets of size 8 can be made using the 10 numeric digits 0 through 9?    How many multi sets of size 8 can be made using the 10 numeric digits 0 through 9?                 sets. We must select 8 of the 10 digits to put in the set.    Use stars and bars: each star represents one of the 8 elements of the set, each bar represents a switch between digits. So there are 8 stars and 9 bars, giving us sets.        "
