  "body": "differentiable functions generalized sum rule  Let be differentiable functions. Prove, using induction, that .  You may assume for any differentiable functions and .   You are allowed to assume the base case. For the inductive case, group all but the last function together as one sum of functions, then apply the usual sum of derivatives rule, and then the inductive hypothesis.  "
